ğŸ“Œ Project Overview

This project performs cross-market financial analysis by collecting, storing, and visualizing data from cryptocurrency markets, stock indices, and oil prices.
It uses APIs, SQLite, and Streamlit to build an end-to-end data pipeline and interactive dashboard.

Markets covered:

Cryptocurrencies (Bitcoin, Ethereum, Tether, Top 250 coins)

Stock Indices (S&P 500, NASDAQ, NIFTY 50)

Oil Prices (WTI Crude)

ğŸ§  What This File Does (High-Level Flow)

Fetches real-time & historical data from APIs

Cleans and structures the data using Pandas

Stores data in an SQLite database

Builds a Streamlit web app for visualization & SQL analysis

(Optional) Exposes the app using Cloudflare Tunnel

ğŸ“¦ Libraries / Imports Used
Library	Purpose
requests	Fetch crypto data from CoinGecko API
pandas	Data cleaning, transformation, analysis
yfinance	Fetch stock market data
sqlite3	Store structured data in SQLite database
streamlit	Build interactive dashboard
plotly	Data visualization
datetime	Date handling
time	API throttling
subprocess	Run Cloudflare tunnel
cloudflared	Public URL for Streamlit app
ğŸ”„ Step-by-Step Explanation of the Code
Step 1: Fetch Cryptocurrency Market Data

Uses CoinGecko API

Fetches top 250 cryptocurrencies

Extracts:

Price

Market cap

Rank

Supply

ATH / ATL

Converts data into a Pandas DataFrame

https://api.coingecko.com/api/v3/coins/markets

Step 2: Fetch Crypto Historical Prices

Retrieves 365 days of price data for:

Bitcoin

Ethereum

Tether

Converts timestamps to readable dates

Step 3: Fetch Oil Price Data

Source: GitHub open dataset (WTI Crude Oil)

Filters data between 2020 â€“ 2026

Step 4: Fetch Stock Market Data

Uses Yahoo Finance API via yfinance

Indices:

